1
00:03:15,895 --> 00:03:18,814
We should've talked
at the boatyard.

2
00:03:18,898 --> 00:03:21,150
You don't wanna
talk about it here.

3
00:03:21,234 --> 00:03:25,821
I'm not falling all over
myself to talk about
it much of anywhere, Jack.

4
00:03:25,905 --> 00:03:27,573
How much do you know?

5
00:03:27,657 --> 00:03:28,657
Not much.

6
00:03:33,454 --> 00:03:36,915
The Birmingham one
was in the papers
over a month ago.

7
00:03:38,376 --> 00:03:40,878
The second one in Atlanta
was all over TV.

8
00:03:41,713 --> 00:03:43,088
Did you ever think
about giving me a call?

9
00:03:43,173 --> 00:03:44,840
No.

10
00:03:44,924 --> 00:03:46,466
Why not?

11
00:03:46,551 --> 00:03:48,093
I quit. Remember?

12
00:03:53,016 --> 00:03:54,933
You look all right now.

13
00:03:57,020 --> 00:03:58,729
I am all right.

14
00:04:10,325 --> 00:04:14,536
If you can't
look anymore,
I understand.

15
00:04:15,622 --> 00:04:18,457
Don't try to run
a game down on me, Jack.

16
00:04:24,923 --> 00:04:28,301
If I really didn't need you
to come back, I wouldn't ask.

17
00:04:28,385 --> 00:04:29,844
This guy's on a lunar cycle.

18
00:04:29,929 --> 00:04:33,431
I have three weeks
and a few days until
the next full moon.

19
00:04:33,515 --> 00:04:38,353
We have a better chance
to get him fast if you help.

20
00:05:21,855 --> 00:05:23,648
I'll think about it.

21
00:05:24,566 --> 00:05:26,025
Stay and eat.

22
00:05:36,787 --> 00:05:38,162
Hi, Molly.

23
00:05:50,884 --> 00:05:52,260
Think it'll keep
them out, Dad?

24
00:05:52,344 --> 00:05:53,469
Yep.

25
00:05:55,889 --> 00:05:58,141
How many turtle eggs
do you think are in here?

26
00:05:58,225 --> 00:05:59,225
In this hatchery?

27
00:05:59,310 --> 00:06:01,561
I'll bet there's
40 or 50 of them.

28
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:05,481
Crabs get most
of the newborns, huh?

29
00:06:05,566 --> 00:06:07,358
Yeah, but not now.

30
00:06:07,443 --> 00:06:09,902
These are all gonna
make it, guaranteed.

31
00:06:13,532 --> 00:06:15,783
What about the dogs?
Are they gonna get in here?

32
00:06:15,868 --> 00:06:17,160
They can't dig under.

33
00:06:17,244 --> 00:06:20,038
That's why we bury
the wire down in the sand.

34
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,751
We need more staples, pal.

35
00:06:33,927 --> 00:06:35,345
You're supposed
to be his friend, Jack.

36
00:06:35,429 --> 00:06:38,556
Why didn't you
leave him alone?

37
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:42,685
If he decides
to do it, Molly,

38
00:06:43,479 --> 00:06:46,440
I'll keep him
as far away
from it as I can.

39
00:07:02,332 --> 00:07:03,874
We got it pretty good,
don't we?

40
00:07:03,958 --> 00:07:06,043
We have it more than good.

41
00:07:06,878 --> 00:07:10,172
All that happened to you
before lets you know that.

42
00:07:13,259 --> 00:07:16,470
If I went back,
I'd only look at evidence.

43
00:07:17,806 --> 00:07:20,140
I wouldn't get
deeply involved.

44
00:07:20,642 --> 00:07:23,310
He'd never even
see me or know my name.

45
00:07:23,812 --> 00:07:27,356
If they find him,
they'll have to take
him down, not me.

46
00:07:31,069 --> 00:07:32,778
What do you think?

47
00:07:36,324 --> 00:07:40,077
I think you've already decided
and you're not really asking.

48
00:07:43,331 --> 00:07:44,998
If I were asking?

49
00:07:47,043 --> 00:07:49,044
Stay here with me,

50
00:07:49,504 --> 00:07:51,004
me and Kevin.

51
00:07:51,923 --> 00:07:54,299
But it's selfish,
and I know it.

52
00:08:00,432 --> 00:08:01,765
Come here.

53
00:09:00,283 --> 00:09:04,036
OFFICER: I'll come inside
with you, if you want,
to show you around.

54
00:09:14,590 --> 00:09:16,674
Mr. Crawford said maybe
you'd want to be alone, but...

55
00:09:16,759 --> 00:09:18,259
That's right.

56
00:09:20,095 --> 00:09:23,389
There's a VCR hooked up
in your hotel room.

57
00:09:24,558 --> 00:09:28,895
They transferred
some home movies of both
families onto half-inch VHS.

58
00:09:28,979 --> 00:09:30,230
Thanks.

59
00:11:14,168 --> 00:11:16,419
Intruder entered through
kitchen sliding door.

60
00:11:16,503 --> 00:11:19,213
Used a glass cutter
anchored to a suction cup.

61
00:11:19,298 --> 00:11:21,090
His entry was skillful.

62
00:11:22,843 --> 00:11:25,220
All the prints
are smooth gloves.

63
00:11:25,597 --> 00:11:29,433
Blond hair, strong,
size 12 shoe imprint.

64
00:11:31,186 --> 00:11:35,773
Blood AB positive,
typed from saliva on glass
from licking the suction cup.

65
00:11:36,691 --> 00:11:40,027
Why didn't he care that
he left saliva on the glass?

66
00:11:43,531 --> 00:11:46,367
It was hot out that night,

67
00:11:46,451 --> 00:11:49,578
so inside the house
must have felt cool to him.

68
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:56,251
Intruder cut Charles Leeds'
throat as he was rising,

69
00:11:56,336 --> 00:11:58,337
then shot Mrs. Leeds.

70
00:11:58,421 --> 00:12:00,798
Bullet entered right
of her navel and lodged
in her lumbar spine,

71
00:12:00,882 --> 00:12:03,550
but she died
of strangulation.

72
00:12:03,635 --> 00:12:05,886
Moderate elevation
of serotonin
and marked increase

73
00:12:05,970 --> 00:12:07,388
of free histamine level
in gunshot wound

74
00:12:07,472 --> 00:12:11,392
indicates she lived
at least five minutes
after she was shot.

75
00:12:12,811 --> 00:12:15,396
All her other injuries
were post-mortem.

76
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:20,067
Direction and velocity
of bloodstains on east wall
indicate arterial spray.

77
00:12:20,610 --> 00:12:22,569
Even with his throat cut,
Leeds tried to fight

78
00:12:22,654 --> 00:12:26,115
because the intruder
was moving
to the children's room.

79
00:12:28,410 --> 00:12:30,327
Bloodstains on west wall
of master bedroom

80
00:12:30,412 --> 00:12:33,664
and matted sliding
marks on hall carpet
remain unexplained,

81
00:12:36,126 --> 00:12:39,336
as does superficial ligature
mark around Mr. Leeds' chest,

82
00:12:40,130 --> 00:12:42,506
also believed
to be post-mortem.

83
00:12:46,094 --> 00:12:49,555
What did the killer
do with them
after they were dead?

84
00:13:12,078 --> 00:13:13,662
(PHONE RINGING)

85
00:13:20,128 --> 00:13:22,087
VALERIE ON ANSWERING MACHINE:
Hi, this is Valerie Leeds.

86
00:13:22,172 --> 00:13:23,797
Sorry, I can't come
to the phone right now,

87
00:13:23,882 --> 00:13:26,675
but if you'd like
to leave a message
please do so after the beep,

88
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:28,761
and I'll call you back
as soon as I can.

89
00:13:28,845 --> 00:13:30,262
(ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS)

90
00:13:30,346 --> 00:13:32,139
(DIAL TONE SOUNDING)

91
00:13:43,526 --> 00:13:45,403
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Twenty-ninth floor.

92
00:13:48,032 --> 00:13:49,324
Going up.

93
00:14:09,428 --> 00:14:12,096
When they were dead,

94
00:14:12,181 --> 00:14:14,307
he smashed the mirrors
and began selecting pieces

95
00:14:14,391 --> 00:14:16,684
that he would use
later on Mrs. Leeds.

96
00:14:17,978 --> 00:14:18,978
(SIGHS)

97
00:14:19,063 --> 00:14:23,066
Killing Mr. Leeds
and the children would
take less than a minute.

98
00:14:24,401 --> 00:14:28,071
Mrs. Leeds'
injuries were post-mortem,
four or five minutes later.

99
00:14:28,989 --> 00:14:32,325
What did he do
in the interval?

100
00:14:32,409 --> 00:14:33,576
(SIGHS)

101
00:14:36,163 --> 00:14:38,998
The smeared bloodstains
on the west wall...

102
00:14:46,257 --> 00:14:47,465
(SIGHS)

103
00:15:17,997 --> 00:15:19,581
(PHONE RINGING)

104
00:15:24,378 --> 00:15:25,795
Hello?
WILL: Molly?

105
00:15:26,630 --> 00:15:27,714
MOLLY: Will, is that you?

106
00:15:27,798 --> 00:15:29,299
Yeah, it's me, honey.

107
00:15:30,593 --> 00:15:34,095
Look, I'll call you tomorrow.
Go back to sleep.

108
00:15:35,764 --> 00:15:37,181
I love you.

109
00:15:37,808 --> 00:15:39,475
I love you too, baby.

110
00:16:26,942 --> 00:16:28,859
What are you dreaming?

111
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:36,325
That's something you can't
afford for me to know about,
isn't it?

112
00:16:40,121 --> 00:16:42,373
God, she's lovely,
isn't she?

113
00:16:47,462 --> 00:16:51,840
It was maddening to have
to touch her with rubber
gloves on, wasn't it?

114
00:16:52,717 --> 00:16:55,135
They found talcum
powder on her leg,

115
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:58,097
but there wasn't
any talcum powder
in the bathroom.

116
00:17:03,103 --> 00:17:04,687
The talcum powder came
out of a rubber glove

117
00:17:04,771 --> 00:17:07,231
as you pulled
it off to touch her.

118
00:17:08,900 --> 00:17:12,152
You took off your gloves
to touch her, didn't you?

119
00:17:13,488 --> 00:17:14,905
Didn't you,
you son of a bitch?

120
00:17:14,990 --> 00:17:16,657
You touched her
with your bare hands,

121
00:17:16,741 --> 00:17:19,201
and then you put
your gloves back on.

122
00:17:19,285 --> 00:17:22,079
But while your
gloves were off,

123
00:17:22,163 --> 00:17:25,582
did you open all their eyes
so that they could see you?

124
00:17:38,972 --> 00:17:39,972
JACK: Hello?

125
00:17:40,056 --> 00:17:41,932
Jack, this is Graham.

126
00:17:42,559 --> 00:17:44,351
Is Price still
in Latent Prints?

127
00:17:44,436 --> 00:17:48,188
Yeah, he's in charge
of the Single Print Index now.

128
00:17:48,273 --> 00:17:49,732
What do you got, Will?

129
00:17:49,816 --> 00:17:50,858
Get him to Atlanta.

130
00:17:50,942 --> 00:17:52,693
Atlanta PD swears
they dusted everything,

131
00:17:52,777 --> 00:17:53,819
and their guy is pretty good.

132
00:17:53,903 --> 00:17:55,571
He is good.
He's not as good as Price.

133
00:17:55,655 --> 00:17:57,281
I'll get him on a plane
in the morning.

134
00:17:57,365 --> 00:17:59,825
What do you want him to do?

135
00:18:01,036 --> 00:18:03,370
Dust Mrs. Leeds'
finger and toenails

136
00:18:03,455 --> 00:18:05,414
and the corneas
of all their eyes.

137
00:18:07,292 --> 00:18:09,293
I think he took
off his gloves.

138
00:18:13,298 --> 00:18:16,341
Our people swear
he wore surgeon's gloves
the whole time.

139
00:18:16,426 --> 00:18:18,427
They dusted everything.

140
00:18:18,511 --> 00:18:20,554
Your report
didn't mention eyes.

141
00:18:21,347 --> 00:18:23,891
Why do you think
he took his gloves off?

142
00:18:23,975 --> 00:18:26,352
WILL: Because Mrs. Leeds
was a beautiful woman.

143
00:18:28,022 --> 00:18:30,774
This is what the subject's
teeth looked like.

144
00:18:30,858 --> 00:18:33,485
The Smithsonian in Washington
reconstructed these

145
00:18:33,569 --> 00:18:35,361
from the impressions that
we took of the bite marks

146
00:18:35,446 --> 00:18:36,613
on the Leeds woman here

147
00:18:36,697 --> 00:18:39,949
and the Jacobi woman
in Birmingham last month.

148
00:18:41,410 --> 00:18:44,287
As you can see, he has
pegged lateral incisors,

149
00:18:44,371 --> 00:18:46,790
that's these teeth
here and here.

150
00:18:49,251 --> 00:18:50,543
SPRINGFIELD:
Vice and Narcotics,

151
00:18:50,628 --> 00:18:52,796
you take the K-Y cowboys
and leather bars.

152
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:54,672
Marcus, Whitman,
heads up at the funeral.

153
00:18:54,757 --> 00:18:57,550
The rest of your assignments
are on the sheet. Let's go.

154
00:18:57,635 --> 00:18:59,302
One more thing.

155
00:18:59,386 --> 00:19:02,931
I've heard officers
referring to this killer
as the Tooth Fairy.

156
00:19:03,015 --> 00:19:04,265
ALL LAUGHING)

157
00:19:04,350 --> 00:19:05,433
Well, I don't want
to hear that in public,

158
00:19:05,518 --> 00:19:07,644
and I don't want to see
it in internal memoranda.

159
00:19:07,728 --> 00:19:09,062
That's it.

160
00:19:10,189 --> 00:19:12,023
(OFFICERS CHATTERING)

161
00:19:23,869 --> 00:19:25,954
I know a burglar's
gonna fence what he stole

162
00:19:26,038 --> 00:19:28,373
'cause his motive
is cash money.

163
00:19:28,457 --> 00:19:31,376
I know his motive,
so I go to work on fences.

164
00:19:31,961 --> 00:19:34,295
This guy, we don't
even have motive.

165
00:19:34,713 --> 00:19:37,966
None of us have shit,
and we know it.

166
00:19:38,050 --> 00:19:39,551
WILL: It's in his dreams.

167
00:19:40,302 --> 00:19:42,011
His motive?
WILL: Yeah.

168
00:19:43,556 --> 00:19:45,598
His act fuels his fantasy.

169
00:19:46,142 --> 00:19:47,433
Which is?

170
00:19:48,853 --> 00:19:50,061
I don't know.

171
00:19:50,187 --> 00:19:51,980
The commissioner was saying
that you're the one

172
00:19:52,064 --> 00:19:54,440
who got Garrett Jacob Hobbs,

173
00:19:54,525 --> 00:19:56,901
and then Dr. Lecktor
three years ago.

174
00:19:57,194 --> 00:19:58,945
Lecktor killed nine
people, didn't he?

175
00:19:59,029 --> 00:20:01,614
Nine that we know of.
Two didn't die.

176
00:20:02,658 --> 00:20:04,534
What happened to them?

177
00:20:05,077 --> 00:20:06,828
One's on a respirator
at a hospital in Baltimore,

178
00:20:06,912 --> 00:20:09,164
the other's in a private
mental hospital in Denver.

179
00:20:09,248 --> 00:20:12,709
What did the psychologists
say was wrong with Lecktor?

180
00:20:12,835 --> 00:20:14,169
(SNICKERS)

181
00:20:14,253 --> 00:20:16,671
The psychologists
call him a psychopath.

182
00:20:17,089 --> 00:20:19,340
They don't know
what else to call him.

183
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:25,263
I understand
he cut you
pretty good.

184
00:20:29,101 --> 00:20:30,894
What about the dog?

185
00:20:33,189 --> 00:20:37,150
It's at the vet's. The kids
brought it in with a puncture
wound in the abdomen.

186
00:20:37,234 --> 00:20:39,444
The Jacobis in Birmingham
had a cat, didn't they?

187
00:20:39,528 --> 00:20:40,862
That's right.

188
00:20:41,614 --> 00:20:45,075
We found
a litter box downstairs,
but we didn't find a cat.

189
00:20:45,452 --> 00:20:48,704
Why don't you get
Birmingham PD a methane
probe out of Washington,

190
00:20:48,788 --> 00:20:50,372
have them cover
the back yard.

191
00:20:50,457 --> 00:20:53,417
Maybe the cat's dead
and the kids buried it.

192
00:20:53,501 --> 00:20:55,044
(PHONE RINGING)

193
00:20:55,337 --> 00:20:56,337
SPRINGFIELD: Yeah?

194
00:20:56,421 --> 00:20:57,463
OVER PHONE:
This is Jimmy Price, FBI.

195
00:20:58,465 --> 00:20:59,882
Let me put you
on speakerphone.

196
00:20:59,966 --> 00:21:01,467
Who am I talking to?

197
00:21:01,551 --> 00:21:02,593
Jimmy, it's Jack Crawford.

198
00:21:02,677 --> 00:21:03,844
You got Will Graham here, too.

199
00:21:03,929 --> 00:21:07,264
I got a partial print
with a tented arch,
it's probably a thumb.

200
00:21:07,349 --> 00:21:11,143
And the fragment
of a palm off the nail
of Mrs. Leeds' left big toe.

201
00:21:11,311 --> 00:21:14,146
Thumbprint came off
the oldest kid's left eye.

202
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:15,856
It stood out against
an eight-ball hemorrhage

203
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:17,066
from the gunshot wound.

204
00:21:17,150 --> 00:21:18,984
Can we make
an identification
off of it?

205
00:21:19,069 --> 00:21:22,363
Maybe,
if he's ever been printed
and he's in my index.

206
00:21:22,864 --> 00:21:24,365
I want to work these up
in my own darkroom.

207
00:21:24,449 --> 00:21:26,659
I'll fax the prints
down to you this afternoon.

208
00:21:26,743 --> 00:21:28,160
Thanks, Jimmy.

209
00:21:34,251 --> 00:21:36,168
(REPORTERS CHATTERING)

210
00:21:41,758 --> 00:21:43,092
No comment.

211
00:21:46,513 --> 00:21:48,973
JACK: If we get lucky
with that print, we're in,

212
00:21:49,057 --> 00:21:50,474
if Jimmy can find
him in the index

213
00:21:50,558 --> 00:21:52,059
and if he's ever been printed.

214
00:21:52,143 --> 00:21:53,102
If not, I don't know.
Hey, Will Graham!

215
00:21:53,186 --> 00:21:55,104
What do you say?
You remember me?

216
00:21:55,188 --> 00:21:57,106
Freddie Lounds,
covered the Lecktor case
for the Tattler,

217
00:21:57,190 --> 00:21:58,482
did the paperback.

218
00:21:58,566 --> 00:22:00,818
So, Will, when did
they call you in?
What do you got?

219
00:22:00,902 --> 00:22:02,069
Hey, look, I'm buying lunch.

220
00:22:02,153 --> 00:22:03,279
Lounds, why don't
you give it a rest?

221
00:22:03,363 --> 00:22:05,531
Hey, he's news.
I'm doing my job.

222
00:22:05,615 --> 00:22:09,076
So, how does this guy
compare with Lecktor?
How does he do them?

223
00:22:10,453 --> 00:22:12,037
How's he do them, Will?

224
00:22:13,873 --> 00:22:14,873
(GROANS)

225
00:22:14,958 --> 00:22:16,792
Keep the fuck away from me.

226
00:22:16,876 --> 00:22:18,127
JACK: Will, Will.

227
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:29,096
Son of a bitch snuck
into the hospital while
I was sedated after Lecktor.

228
00:22:29,180 --> 00:22:31,432
He pulled back the sheets,
and he took pictures.

229
00:22:31,516 --> 00:22:32,558
Yeah, I know.

230
00:22:32,642 --> 00:22:34,810
Look, don't expect
too much from me,
all right?

231
00:22:34,894 --> 00:22:37,062
We only got
three weeks left,
and you're our best shot.

232
00:22:37,147 --> 00:22:40,065
You think I'm gonna see
him standing in the street
and say, "There he is"?

233
00:22:40,150 --> 00:22:42,735
That's Houdini
you're thinking about.

234
00:22:44,654 --> 00:22:47,614
The Tooth Fairy's
gonna go on until
we get smart or get lucky.

235
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:48,657
He won't stop.

236
00:22:48,742 --> 00:22:49,783
Why?

237
00:22:50,493 --> 00:22:52,536
He's got a genuine
taste for it.

238
00:22:52,620 --> 00:22:55,372
You do know
something about him.

239
00:22:56,624 --> 00:22:58,083
Not enough.

240
00:23:01,212 --> 00:23:03,339
I think I'll go see
Lecktor tomorrow.

241
00:23:03,423 --> 00:23:04,674
Why?

242
00:23:06,093 --> 00:23:07,761
Recover the mindset.

243
00:23:40,503 --> 00:23:44,964
That's the same atrocious
aftershave you wore
in court three years ago.

244
00:23:45,049 --> 00:23:47,342
Yeah, I keep
getting it for Christmas.

245
00:23:51,472 --> 00:23:53,348
Did you get my card?

246
00:23:53,432 --> 00:23:54,474
I got it. Thank you.

247
00:23:55,226 --> 00:23:58,728
How is Officer Stewart?
The one who was first
to see my basement.

248
00:23:58,813 --> 00:24:00,313
Stewart's fine.

249
00:24:00,398 --> 00:24:02,524
Emotional problems, I hear.

250
00:24:02,608 --> 00:24:04,192
Do you have
any problems, Will?

251
00:24:04,276 --> 00:24:05,610
No.

252
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:07,779
No, of course you don't.

253
00:24:07,863 --> 00:24:09,239
(SNICKERS)

254
00:24:09,990 --> 00:24:12,283
I'm glad you came.

255
00:24:12,618 --> 00:24:15,328
My callers are mostly
clinical psychologists

256
00:24:15,413 --> 00:24:17,705
from cornfield
universities somewhere.

257
00:24:17,832 --> 00:24:19,457
Second-raters, the lot.

258
00:24:19,542 --> 00:24:21,751
Dr. Bloom
showed me your article
on surgical addiction

259
00:24:21,836 --> 00:24:23,461
in the Journal
of Clinical Psychiatry.

260
00:24:23,546 --> 00:24:24,546
And?

261
00:24:24,630 --> 00:24:25,755
Very interesting.

262
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:27,590
Even to a layman.

263
00:24:29,385 --> 00:24:31,678
I want you to help me,
Dr. Lecktor.

264
00:24:31,762 --> 00:24:34,764
Yes, I thought so.

265
00:24:34,849 --> 00:24:35,974
It's about Atlanta
and Birmingham.

266
00:24:36,058 --> 00:24:37,267
Yes?

267
00:24:37,351 --> 00:24:38,351
You read about it?

268
00:24:38,436 --> 00:24:39,936
In the papers.

269
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:42,230
I don't tear out
the articles.

270
00:24:42,314 --> 00:24:46,317
I wouldn't want them
to think I was dwelling
on anything morbid.

271
00:24:48,821 --> 00:24:51,531
You want to know
how he's choosing
them, don't you?

272
00:24:51,615 --> 00:24:52,782
I thought you might
have some ideas.

273
00:24:52,867 --> 00:24:54,033
Why should I tell you?

274
00:24:54,118 --> 00:24:56,536
You'd get to see
the file on this case.

275
00:24:56,620 --> 00:24:57,620
And there's another reason.

276
00:24:57,705 --> 00:24:58,955
Pray tell.

277
00:24:59,039 --> 00:25:00,373
Thought you might
be curious to see

278
00:25:00,458 --> 00:25:02,125
if you're smarter
than the person
I'm looking for.

279
00:25:02,209 --> 00:25:04,961
Then by implication you think
you're smarter than me,
since you caught me.

280
00:25:05,045 --> 00:25:07,422
No. I know that
I'm not smarter than you.

281
00:25:07,506 --> 00:25:09,132
Then how did you catch me?

282
00:25:09,216 --> 00:25:10,175
You had disadvantages.

283
00:25:10,259 --> 00:25:11,593
What disadvantages?

284
00:25:11,677 --> 00:25:13,136
You're insane.

285
00:25:15,222 --> 00:25:17,056
You are very tan, Will.

286
00:25:18,309 --> 00:25:19,851
Your hands are rough.

287
00:25:21,562 --> 00:25:24,023
They don't look like
cop's hands anymore.

288
00:25:24,649 --> 00:25:27,401
And that shaving lotion
is something
a child would select.

289
00:25:27,486 --> 00:25:29,987
It has a ship
on the bottle,
doesn't it?

290
00:25:32,199 --> 00:25:35,784
Don't think you can
persuade me with appeals
to my intellectual vanity.

291
00:25:35,869 --> 00:25:38,662
I don't think
I'll persuade you at all.

292
00:25:38,747 --> 00:25:41,081
You'll either
do it or you won't.

293
00:25:41,917 --> 00:25:45,503
Besides, we have
Dr. Bloom working on it,
and he's the best.

294
00:25:45,587 --> 00:25:47,338
Do you have
the file with you?
Yes.

295
00:25:47,422 --> 00:25:48,589
Pictures?
Yes.

296
00:25:48,673 --> 00:25:50,382
Let me have them,
and I might consider it.

297
00:25:50,467 --> 00:25:51,800
No.

298
00:25:55,764 --> 00:25:57,264
Dream much, Will?

299
00:25:57,349 --> 00:25:58,974
Goodbye, Dr. Lecktor.

300
00:25:59,601 --> 00:26:02,436
You haven't threatened
to take away my books yet.

301
00:26:04,981 --> 00:26:07,942
Let me have the file,
and I'll tell
you what I think.

302
00:26:14,699 --> 00:26:16,408
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

303
00:26:51,319 --> 00:26:52,987
(PAGES FLIPPING)

304
00:27:09,504 --> 00:27:11,547
This is a very shy boy, Will.

305
00:27:12,549 --> 00:27:13,924
What were their yards like?

306
00:27:14,009 --> 00:27:17,177
Big back yards.
Fences, hedges.

307
00:27:18,763 --> 00:27:19,763
Why?

308
00:27:19,848 --> 00:27:21,140
Because, my dear Will,

309
00:27:21,224 --> 00:27:24,310
if this pilgrim
imagines he has a relationship
with the moon,

310
00:27:24,394 --> 00:27:26,687
he might go outside
to look at it.

311
00:27:28,064 --> 00:27:30,274
Have you ever seen
blood in the moonlight?

312
00:27:30,358 --> 00:27:32,192
It appears quite black.

313
00:27:33,153 --> 00:27:37,406
If one were nude, it would
be better to have privacy
for this sort of thing.

314
00:27:38,491 --> 00:27:39,867
That's interesting.

315
00:27:39,951 --> 00:27:42,202
No, it's not.
You thought of it before.

316
00:27:42,287 --> 00:27:43,788
I considered it.

317
00:27:43,873 --> 00:27:47,167
You came here to look at me,
to get the old scent
back again, didn't you?

318
00:27:47,251 --> 00:27:48,501
I want your opinion.

319
00:27:48,586 --> 00:27:50,170
I don't have one right now.

320
00:27:50,254 --> 00:27:53,006
Well, when you have one,
I'd like to hear it.

321
00:27:53,090 --> 00:27:54,090
Can I keep this?

322
00:27:54,175 --> 00:27:55,175
I haven't decided yet.

323
00:27:55,259 --> 00:27:56,468
I'll study them.

324
00:27:56,552 --> 00:27:58,303
When you get more files,
I'd like to see them, too.

325
00:27:58,387 --> 00:28:01,806
You can call me.
When I have to call my lawyer,
they bring me a telephone.

326
00:28:01,891 --> 00:28:05,185
Would you like to leave me
your home phone number?

327
00:28:05,728 --> 00:28:06,770
No.

328
00:28:08,731 --> 00:28:09,814
Do you know
how you caught me?

329
00:28:09,899 --> 00:28:11,775
Goodbye, Dr. Lecktor.
You can leave
messages for me.

330
00:28:11,859 --> 00:28:15,111
LECKTOR: Do you know
how you caught me?

331
00:28:15,196 --> 00:28:18,573
The reason you caught me,
Will, is we're just alike.

332
00:28:19,075 --> 00:28:20,492
Do you understand?

333
00:28:22,244 --> 00:28:23,912
Smell yourself.

334
00:28:29,543 --> 00:28:31,836
(PANTING)

335
00:29:39,739 --> 00:29:41,156
(CLICKING)

336
00:29:42,324 --> 00:29:43,324
Gotcha.

337
00:29:45,244 --> 00:29:48,538
WOMAN ON PA:217
now boarding at Gate 12.

338
00:29:48,622 --> 00:29:54,586
Eastern Airlines
Flight 217 is now ready
for boarding at Gate 12.

339
00:30:01,135 --> 00:30:03,095
Get up against the bunk
and face the wall.

340
00:30:03,180 --> 00:30:06,766
Don't turn around,
or I'll Mace you
in the face.

341
00:30:20,322 --> 00:30:21,530
Thank you so much.

342
00:30:21,615 --> 00:30:23,199
I'll call you
when I'm finished.

343
00:30:32,959 --> 00:30:34,084
FEMALE OPERATOR:
Are you ready for your call?

344
00:30:34,169 --> 00:30:35,628
Yes, thank you.

345
00:30:35,712 --> 00:30:37,296
(PHONE RINGING)

346
00:30:38,048 --> 00:30:40,466
WOMAN 1: Paltrow,
Christiansen & Golub,
Law Offices.

347
00:30:40,550 --> 00:30:42,760
Excuse me.
I must have misdialed.

348
00:30:46,723 --> 00:30:48,265
(PHONE RINGING)

349
00:30:52,020 --> 00:30:55,147
MALE OPERATOR:
Thank you for using AT&T.
This is Operator 24.

350
00:30:55,899 --> 00:30:59,527
Operator, I don't
have the use of my arms.

351
00:30:59,611 --> 00:31:03,823
Would you be so kind
as to dial a number
for me, please?

352
00:31:04,074 --> 00:31:05,825
Certainly. What's the number?

353
00:31:05,909 --> 00:31:07,618
Area code 301,

354
00:31:07,702 --> 00:31:11,497
555-6624.

355
00:31:11,581 --> 00:31:13,082
(PHONE DIALING)

356
00:31:15,043 --> 00:31:17,753
WOMAN 2:
The University of Chicago,
Department of Psychiatry.

357
00:31:17,838 --> 00:31:19,713
Dr. Sidney Bloom, please.

358
00:31:19,798 --> 00:31:22,091
He's not in,
but I'll connect you
to his office.

359
00:31:22,175 --> 00:31:23,592
What's his
secretary's
name again?

360
00:31:23,677 --> 00:31:26,262
Martha King.
Just a moment, please.

361
00:31:27,931 --> 00:31:28,889
WOMAN 3: Martha King's desk.

362
00:31:28,974 --> 00:31:29,974
Hi, Martha.

363
00:31:30,308 --> 00:31:32,268
Martha doesn't
come in nights.

364
00:31:33,353 --> 00:31:35,020
Maybe you can help me.

365
00:31:35,105 --> 00:31:37,690
This is Bob Greer
of Blaine & Edwards
publishing company,

366
00:31:37,774 --> 00:31:39,859
Dr. Bloom asked me
to send a copy

367
00:31:39,943 --> 00:31:41,694
of The Psychiatrist
and the Law to someone.

368
00:31:41,778 --> 00:31:44,321
Martha never sent me
the address and phone number.

369
00:31:44,406 --> 00:31:45,865
She'll be in in the morning.

370
00:31:45,949 --> 00:31:49,368
Well, I've got to catch
Federal Express in about
five minutes.

371
00:31:49,452 --> 00:31:52,580
I'd be immensely appreciative
if you could pull it out
of her Rolodex for me.

372
00:31:52,664 --> 00:31:53,998
I don't see a Rolodex.

373
00:31:54,082 --> 00:31:56,792
I'll bet she has a call caddy
right next to her phone.

374
00:31:56,877 --> 00:31:58,669
Yeah...
Well, zip that
little pointer

375
00:31:58,753 --> 00:32:00,921
right on down
to the letter G.

376
00:32:01,006 --> 00:32:02,131
All right.

377
00:32:02,382 --> 00:32:05,467
The name we're looking for,
last name Graham,

378
00:32:05,552 --> 00:32:07,219
the man the book
is supposed
to be sent to,

379
00:32:07,304 --> 00:32:09,763
a Mr. Will Graham.

380
00:32:09,848 --> 00:32:12,850
Federal Bureau
of Investigation,
10th and Pennsylvania,

381
00:32:12,934 --> 00:32:14,184
Washington, D.C.

382
00:32:14,269 --> 00:32:18,230
Now, I'll bet it has his
home address there, too.

383
00:32:18,315 --> 00:32:21,817
3680 DeSoto Highway,
Captiva, Florida.

384
00:32:23,321 --> 00:32:25,822
Thank you so very much.

385
00:32:28,326 --> 00:32:29,659
(TAPPING)

386
00:32:29,827 --> 00:32:31,161
I've finished.

387
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:37,709
(PASSENGERS CHATTERING)

388
00:34:11,846 --> 00:34:12,846
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

389
00:34:12,930 --> 00:34:14,347
Mom!
Oh, my gosh.

390
00:34:14,432 --> 00:34:16,266
It's all right. Stewardess!

391
00:34:30,573 --> 00:34:31,656
CAPTAIN ON PA SYSTEM:
Ladies and gentlemen,

392
00:34:31,741 --> 00:34:34,451
we are beginning our descent
into Birmingham.

393
00:36:34,447 --> 00:36:37,491
WILL: You used a cutting
tool on the branch
so that you could see.

394
00:36:37,576 --> 00:36:39,743
Then you passed
the time whittling

395
00:36:40,787 --> 00:36:42,496
and dreaming.

396
00:36:44,499 --> 00:36:46,000
When night came,

397
00:36:46,960 --> 00:36:49,753
you saw them pass by
their bright windows.

398
00:36:50,338 --> 00:36:52,756
Then you watched
the shades go down,

399
00:36:53,592 --> 00:36:56,343
then you saw the lights
go out, one by one.

400
00:36:56,845 --> 00:36:58,888
Then after a while,
you climbed down

401
00:36:58,972 --> 00:37:01,182
and you went in to them,
didn't you?

402
00:37:01,266 --> 00:37:02,350
Didn't you,
you son of a bitch?

403
00:37:02,435 --> 00:37:05,270
You watched them
all goddamned day long!

404
00:37:08,524 --> 00:37:10,650
That's why houses
with big yards.

405
00:37:15,573 --> 00:37:18,658
WILL: I need Firearms
and Tool Marks section
out here on a severed branch.

406
00:37:18,743 --> 00:37:20,410
I need to know what kind
of cutting tool he used.

407
00:37:20,494 --> 00:37:22,579
And then I need
Bowman in Documents
to fall on this carving.

408
00:37:22,663 --> 00:37:23,663
JACK: Is it weird?

409
00:37:23,748 --> 00:37:24,998
The mark? Yeah.

410
00:37:25,291 --> 00:37:27,876
If Documents
can't do the carving,
I'll send it up to Langley.

411
00:37:27,960 --> 00:37:29,878
WILL: Did Price
get an identification
off the Leeds print?

412
00:37:29,962 --> 00:37:31,838
No, Price hasn't found
him in the index yet.

413
00:37:31,923 --> 00:37:34,424
It's a hand search.
He's got half
his department on it.

414
00:37:34,508 --> 00:37:37,052
Listen, have you seen
this week's Tattler?

415
00:37:37,303 --> 00:37:39,721
(SCOFFS) It's not on my
preferred reading list.

416
00:37:39,805 --> 00:37:40,889
Well,

417
00:37:40,973 --> 00:37:43,350
your picture's
all over the front page.

418
00:37:45,436 --> 00:37:46,394
Who the hell was it? Lounds?

419
00:37:46,479 --> 00:37:47,896
Of course. Who else?

420
00:37:47,980 --> 00:37:49,856
God damn it, Jack!

421
00:37:49,941 --> 00:37:52,567
I promised Molly!
I promised her!

422
00:37:54,779 --> 00:37:55,946
Come in.

423
00:37:56,155 --> 00:37:57,656
GUARD: Dr. Chilton?

424
00:37:58,157 --> 00:37:59,366
Yes?

425
00:37:59,450 --> 00:38:01,409
When we were cleaning
out Dr. Lecktor's cell,

426
00:38:01,494 --> 00:38:03,328
he heard us coming
and hid something
in a book.

427
00:38:03,412 --> 00:38:04,704
We got him
out of there
and dug around.

428
00:38:04,789 --> 00:38:06,539
Is that it?
Yes.

429
00:38:06,624 --> 00:38:08,959
Put it down
on my desk, Bonner.

430
00:38:16,842 --> 00:38:18,343
Has anyone else
seen this except you?

431
00:38:18,427 --> 00:38:20,178
No.

432
00:38:23,432 --> 00:38:25,183
SECRETARY: Special Agent
Crawford's office.

433
00:38:25,268 --> 00:38:26,434
This is Dr. Chilton.

434
00:38:26,519 --> 00:38:28,228
I need to speak
to Mr. Graham right away.

435
00:38:28,312 --> 00:38:29,729
He's not here,
he's in Birmingham.

436
00:38:29,814 --> 00:38:31,773
Special Agent Crawford
is on the line with him now.

437
00:38:31,857 --> 00:38:33,942
Please tell them
this is very, very urgent.

438
00:38:34,026 --> 00:38:35,026
I'll hold on.

439
00:38:38,823 --> 00:38:40,198
Dr. Chilton,
it's Jack Crawford.

440
00:38:40,283 --> 00:38:41,783
You have Will Graham
on the line, too.

441
00:38:41,867 --> 00:38:44,953
CHILTON: I have a note,
or two pieces of a note

442
00:38:45,037 --> 00:38:47,831
that appears to be
from that man who killed
those people in Atlanta.

443
00:38:47,915 --> 00:38:49,666
Where did you get it?

444
00:38:49,750 --> 00:38:51,793
In Hannibal Lecktor's cell.
It was hidden in a book.

445
00:38:51,877 --> 00:38:55,046
WILL: Don't touch the note.
Can you read it to us?

446
00:38:55,381 --> 00:38:57,340
It's written
on toilet tissue.

447
00:38:58,217 --> 00:39:00,385
"My dear Dr. Lecktor,

448
00:39:00,469 --> 00:39:04,514
"I wanted to tell you
I'm delighted that you've
taken an interest in me.

449
00:39:04,598 --> 00:39:08,310
"I know that you alone
can understand
what I am becoming.

450
00:39:08,561 --> 00:39:12,814
"You alone know
the people I use
to help me in these things

451
00:39:12,898 --> 00:39:15,567
"are only elements
undergoing change

452
00:39:15,651 --> 00:39:19,487
"to fuel the radiance
of what I am becoming,

453
00:39:19,572 --> 00:39:22,450
"just as the source
of light is burning.

454
00:39:23,869 --> 00:39:26,579
"I have a collection
of your press clippings.

455
00:39:27,039 --> 00:39:29,665
"I think they are absurd,
as are mine.

456
00:39:30,167 --> 00:39:33,753
"'The Tooth Fairy,'
what could be
more inappropriate?

457
00:39:34,087 --> 00:39:37,006
"Investigator Graham
interests me,

458
00:39:37,090 --> 00:39:39,050
"very purposeful-looking.

459
00:39:39,134 --> 00:39:41,761
"I hope we can correspond."

460
00:39:41,845 --> 00:39:43,304
There's a piece missing here.

461
00:39:43,388 --> 00:39:45,139
Now I'll read
the bottom part.

462
00:39:45,891 --> 00:39:47,641
"After I hear back from you,

463
00:39:47,726 --> 00:39:49,852
"I might send
you something wet."

464
00:39:49,936 --> 00:39:51,479
Signed "Avid Fan."

465
00:39:52,814 --> 00:39:55,191
It has teeth marks
pressed into it
at the bottom.

466
00:39:55,275 --> 00:39:58,069
Order a chopper,
next thing smoking.
I don't care whose it is.

467
00:39:58,153 --> 00:40:00,029
Two, call Alabama
Air National Guard,

468
00:40:00,113 --> 00:40:01,989
get Graham back
here right now.

469
00:40:02,074 --> 00:40:04,033
Then call Documents
and tell them
to scramble a team.

470
00:40:04,117 --> 00:40:06,369
I want everybody moving
five minutes ago.
You understand?

471
00:40:06,453 --> 00:40:08,287
JACK: I have a Documents
team on its way to you

472
00:40:08,372 --> 00:40:09,747
by helicopter
to pick up the note.

473
00:40:09,831 --> 00:40:11,207
Listen, after we've
worked the note,

474
00:40:11,291 --> 00:40:12,625
I want to replace
it in Lecktor's cell.

475
00:40:12,709 --> 00:40:14,210
I don't want Lecktor to know
that we've found it,

476
00:40:14,294 --> 00:40:16,253
he might try to warn
the killer somehow.

477
00:40:16,338 --> 00:40:17,338
Where's Lecktor now?

478
00:40:17,422 --> 00:40:18,547
CHILTON: Holding cell.

479
00:40:18,632 --> 00:40:20,883
How long can you keep
him in there without
him getting suspicious?

480
00:40:20,967 --> 00:40:22,927
CHILTON: Three, four hours.

481
00:40:23,011 --> 00:40:25,054
Brian, we have a note
coming in on the flight,

482
00:40:25,138 --> 00:40:27,807
possibly from the Tooth Fairy,
number one priority.

483
00:40:27,891 --> 00:40:29,058
It has to go
to Hair and Fiber,

484
00:40:29,142 --> 00:40:30,393
Latent Prints,
and then Documents.

485
00:40:30,477 --> 00:40:32,353
Will Graham and I
will be walking it through.

486
00:41:11,685 --> 00:41:14,645
One hair, Graham.
Maybe half an inch.

487
00:41:16,148 --> 00:41:17,481
And a couple of blue grains.

488
00:41:17,566 --> 00:41:19,775
Work the hair.

489
00:41:19,860 --> 00:41:21,819
What do we have
for negative comparison?

490
00:41:21,903 --> 00:41:26,115
Hair from Lecktor's comb,
whiskers from Lecktor's
razor they let him use.

